column1: For every Emergency Department encounter, hospitals may report a Principal External Cause of Injury/Morbidity and up to 4 Other External Cause of Injuries/Morbidities.  The E-Code Frequency Report shows the frequency, in each position, of the reporting of each code.
Ecode = the external cause of injury/morbidity, according to ICD-9-CM/ICD-10-CM.
ICD-9-CM (International Classification of Diseases, 9th Revision, Clinical Modification), effective for encounters prior to October 1, 2015.
ICD-10-CM (International Classification of Diseases, 10th Revision, Clinical Modification), effective for encounters beginning October 1, 2015.
TotalECodes = the total number of times the E-Code was reported in a Principal or Other E-Code position.
e0 = the total number of times the E-Code was reported as a Principal External Cause of Injury/Morbidity.
e1-e4 = the total number of times the E-Code was reported in each Other External Cause of Injury/Morbidity position.
Data Source: California Emergency Department Database, Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
